						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the Ādiliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājadēva (I): Year 24 = 1008-09 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in Vaṭṭeḻuttu script is damaged. It records a gift of sheep for two perpetual lamps to the god of the temple of Śūraṅguḍi-nāṭṭīchchuvaram of Ādaṉūr in Śūraṅguḍi-nāḍu by •••• kaṉ-Araiyaṉ on behalf of two persons including Eṭṭi. The gift of 25 sheep each was entrusted to four individuals including •••• kkan-Tama[rā]kki, Kaṇakkaṉ Iruṅkīraṉ, Kaṇattāreṭṭi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Seṅgōḍaṉ-Maśaiyaṉ, a shepherd from Perumpulivalam.</p>						

						</summary>
